# Force Dynamic on Data Pages

Any page or layout that calls `readData()` (directly or via a server component) **must** declare:

```ts
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";
```

Place it at the top of the file, right after imports.

## Why

Next.js 16 tries to statically pre-render all pages at build time. `readData()` attempts a
Neon connection during the build → ETIMEDOUT → build crash. `force-dynamic` tells Next.js
to render this page at request time only.

## Which pages need it

| File | Needs it? |
|------|-----------|
| `src/app/page.tsx` | ✅ yes — calls `readData()` |
| `src/app/settings/page.tsx` | ✅ yes — calls `readData()` |
| Any new page that imports from `@/lib/store` | ✅ yes |
| `/login`, `/register` | ❌ no — pure client components |
| API routes | ❌ no — always dynamic |

## Do not use `revalidate`

Do not set `export const revalidate = N` as a substitute — it still pre-renders once at build.
Use `force-dynamic` exclusively for pages that depend on live DB state.
